member.name: HTTP_SERVICE_CONFIG_URLACL_SET
member.summary: TheHTTP_SERVICE_CONFIG_URLACL_SET structure is used to add a new record to the URL reservation store or retrieve an existing record from it. An instance of the structure is used to pass data in through the pConfigInformation parameter of the function, or to retrieve data through the pOutputConfigInformation parameter of the function when the ConfigId parameter of either function is equal to HTTPServiceConfigUrlAclInfo.

member.name: HTTP_SERVICE_CONFIG_URLACL_SET.KeyDesc
member.summary: An structure that identifies the URL reservation record.

member.name: HTTP_SERVICE_CONFIG_URLACL_SET.ParamDesc
member.summary: An structure that holds the contents of the specified URL reservation record.
